AU  - Schmenner, Roger W.
T1  - Choosing New Industrial Capacity: On-Site EXpansion, Branching, and Relocation*
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885351
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 95
IS  - 1
SP  - 103
EP  - 119
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A manufacturing firm can increase its capacity through expansion at existing sites, opening new plants, or relocating to new, larger space. These options are in fact not very good substitutes for one another. This paper argues why one might be preferred to the others and supports its view of the capacity choice with detailed evidence from over 400 plants in New England.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885351
ER  - 



