TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ofer, Gur
AU  - Pickersgill, Joyce
T1  - Soviet Household Saving: A Cross-Section Study of Soviet Emigrant Families*
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885352
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 95
IS  - 1
SP  - 121
EP  - 144
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This study examines the saving patterns of Soviet households by developing a saving function based on cross-section data derived from a family budget survey of Soviet emigrants. The results are very similar to those of Western studies. While saving is a positive function of current income, the average rate of saving rises only relatively mildly with income, indicating that current income from the public sector is much more “permanent” than in market economies. The proportion of income earned from the private sector that is saved is much higher—indicating that it is highly transitory and risky. The long-run saving rate is, by international comparison, rather low.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885352
ER  - 



